    projectStructure: 'To clarify the information architecture, I mapped the product into a tree structure separating global workspaces - Dashboard, Calendar, and Notes / References - from project-specific views such as Project Overview, Stage View, and the Event Details modal. The diagram also marks the key interactive moments in the prototype, including creating a new project and managing stage tasks, milestones, notes, and references.',
    projectStructureImage: projectStructureImg,
    earlyWireframes: 'Before moving into high-fidelity prototyping, I created low-fidelity page drafts to test the product\'s information hierarchy, navigation flow, and the relationship between global workspaces and project-specific views. These wireframes focused on structure first, helping me evaluate how dashboard, project, calendar, and reference screens could work together as one planning system.',
